cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper discusses a data plane programming framework for OpenFlow-based SDN deployments, which falls under the category of network architecture and protocols (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the ability to program heterogeneous forwarding elements, which could be considered a security concern (cs.CR) as well as an aspect of computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses an abstract instruction set, which could be considered a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL).
